snippet.title: The Power of the Gospel | A Story of Forgiveness
snippet.description: The Gospel transforms lives and heals broken hearts. A woman heard one of Dr. LaDonna's radio programs broadcast among the Runyankole people in Northern Uganda . She was preparing to commit suicide because of the anguish of her heart. The witchdoctor had taken her child and sacrificed her to cancel the spread of Covid. The woman fell into deep depression and she lost the will to live. But when she heard the Good News of Jesus’ love and sacrifice for her, she chose to follow Him. She called the radio station and reported, “I was going to take my life. But when I heard that Jesus died for me, I knew that I didn’t have to die. Now I want to live!” This woman contacted the pastor (who has served as my interpreter) and said, “Come with me to the grave of my daughter. I want to pray and forgive the man who sacrificed her.” THIS IS THE POWER OF THE GOSPEL to heal hearts.

snippet.title: The Gospel Icon Video | Osborn Ministries International
snippet.description: http://www.Osborn.org/ Although the Bible is a multi-faceted book, written over a period of 2000 years by more than 40 different authors, it contains a remarkably simple message of God's redemption plan for people that is commonly known as the gospel. Once you understand the overarching message of the gospel, you can then discover your own divine purpose as you learn how to live as the unique person God has created you to be.

snippet.title: DocuMiracle - Java Harvest | Osborn Ministries International
snippet.description:
This clip is a portion of all that God did in Java.  To purchase the entire Video go to http://www.Osborn.org.

Each film portrays the power of the gospel in action. No fictional stories, drama or actors are involved. Each production is authentic and documentary. Overwhelming is a one-word
description of this dynamic 11 DVD series of the ongoing Osborn ministry legacy reaching thousands of lives in over 80 nations!

The Osborns have been a dynamic and influential force in world evangelism proclaiming and demonstrating the gospel. Christ showing Himself alive with signs and wonders is the ongoing 
evidence that Jesus Christ is the same  yesterday, today and forever.
